article.headline: Nevada 112, Houston 99
article.story: RENO, Nev. -- Joey Shaw scored 26 points to lead Nevada to a 112-99 victory over Houston on Saturday night. Brandon Fields added 24 points and Armon Johnson 22 points and 12 assists for the Wolf Pack (2-1). Aubrey Coleman scored 34 points and Adam Brown 25 for the Cougars (1-1). Luke Babbitt had 14 points and 17 rebounds for Nevada. The Wolf Pack led by as many as 26 points, 84-58 with 13:52 left, before Houston rallied to pull to within 100-94 on a three-point play by Desmond Wade with 5 minutes left. Nevada responded with a 8-0 run, including six points by Shaw, to put the game out of reach. Nevada led 61-44 at halftime, sparked by the hot hand of Fields who had 22 points in the first half on 9 of 11 shooting.
